Age distribution of RSV hospitalizations (data frame)

Source: R/age_distribution.R
age_distribution.Rd

A data frame showing the age distribution of RSV hospitalizations. Data is available for the 7 states that began participation in RSV-Net in 2016.

Usage

age_distribution

Format

age_distribution

A data frame with 42 rows and 3 columns:

state

state name (California, Georgia, Maryland, Minnesota, New York, Tennessee, Oregon)

age_group

age group (<6 months, 6-11 months, 1-4 years, 5-64 years, 65-74 years, 75+ years)

proportion

proportion of RSV hospitalizations during the 2018-2019 and 2029-2020 seasons

...

Source

https://data.cdc.gov/Public-Health-Surveillance/Weekly-Rates-of-Laboratory-Confirmed-RSV-Hospitali/29hc-w46k/about_data
